title: For Sale:  "Draco" AK-47
location: N. Columbus/Harris Co., Columbus, GA, Georgia
postcontent:
For sale is a nearly new Romanian "Draco" AK-47. Legally,these are imported as pistols,not rifles, therefore they are not bound by the regulation (usc 922r) limiting foreign made parts in assault rifles. This means that the ENTIRE weapon was made in the Romanian Cugir arsenal, where they make their military weapons. Most AK's circulating in the states have been re-manufactured, by law, from a mix of foreign and US made parts. So,while this is a Romanian weapon, and even imported by Century Arms , it hasn't been cobbled together out of mismatched,used parts by the infamous "ham-fisted chimps at CAI", like the sometimes-questionable WASR AK's. This is ALL genuine East Block AK, the reciever,trigger,chrome-lined barrel,etc. and everything is straight,solid and very well put together.
 I've added a few extras, like a Picatinny/tactical rail forend, a sling mount adapter and a high-end sling, a Krinkov flash hider, and a slightly larger after-market grip ( or I could put the original Bake-lite grip back on it.) I'm also including the original wood fore-grips, as well as a couple boxes of good Russian ammo.
 (Now, the usual fine print: No checks, no shipping, FTF local cash sale only, purchaser MUST be over 21 and Georgia resident, with valid ID to prove it. I will not respond to scammers asking if "the item is still for sale". If the ad is still up, it's still for sale. I'm the original purchaser, and Ga. resident with my Ga. The Zastava M57 pistol, was the standard sidearm of the Yugoslavian army. Adopted in 1957, it was a licensed produced copy of the Soviet Tokarev TT pistol, although the M57 had a longer grip that hosted a longer magazine (9 rounds versus 8 rounds in TT). In around 1970 Crvena Zastava began production of the similar pistol.

This pistol is the M57a, it's the same as the M57 but it has an external safety. These are new pistols.

title: For Sale:  Draco AK-47
postcontent:
For sale is a nearly new Romanian "Draco" AK-47. Legally,these are imported as pistols,not rifles, therefore they are not bound by the regulation (usc 922r) limiting foreign made parts in assault rifles. This means that the ENTIRE weapon was made in the Romanian Cugir arsenal, where they make their military weapons. Most AK's circulating in the states have been re-manufactured, by law, from a mix of foreign and US made parts. So,while this is a Romanian weapon, and even imported by Century Arms , it hasn't been cobbled together out of mismatched,used parts by the infamous "ham-fisted chimps at CAI", like the sometimes-questionable WASR AK's. This is ALL genuine,new East Block AK; the reciever,trigger,chrome-lined barrel,etc. and everything is straight,solid and very well put together.
I've added a few extras, like a Picatinny/tactical rail forend, a sling mount adapter and a very nice sling, a Krinkov flash hider, and a slightly larger after-market grip ( or I could put the original Bake-lite grip back on it.) I'm also including the original wood grips, as well as a couple boxes of good Russian ammo.
(Now, the usual fine print: No checks, no shipping, FTF local cash sale only, purchaser MUST be over 21 and Georgia resident, with valid ID to prove it. I'm the original purchaser, and have my Ga. CCW permit, so everything's cool on my end. )
Thanks..........M.

title: For Sale:  Saiga AK (Izhmash) New in Box w/1x10rd Mag + Hard Case + 6 Position Stock + Ammo & Extra Mags Avail.
postcontent:
For Sale NIB Saiga AK74 5.45x39 (Izhmash) With A bunch of Extras.

First off in case you didn't know, the 5.45x39 Rd is the russian predecessor to the 7.62x39, made in response to the skinnier, longer american made .223/.556 rd around the time of the vietnam war or after. Its a lightweight and very accurate round, thus making the Ak74 a way more accurate rifle than the earlier ak47's.

I have for sale a very very nice brand new in box, fired 50rds to make sure it cycles properly, flawless response. title: For Sale:  CZ Cold War 9mm Pistol
postcontent:
CZ Cold War pistol - In excellent condition, no scratches, damage, excuses. Low round count. Includes the original box, qty: 2 Factory CZ 17 round magazines, documentation, and cleaning kit. Limited to 999 pistols worldwide - long out of production. 

This pistol has an all black finish with a Red Star near the muzzle on both sides of the pistol and it comes with two 16 round mags. It has glow in the dark sights, not Tritium. There is a Soviet hammer and sickle laser engraved on the right hand side of the frame above the grip. The trigger pull appears to be similar to the original Cold War era hefty East Bloc trigger pull. The rollmarks are in Cyrillic script and state “ Model 75 Cal. 9 Para” and “Manufactured in Czechoslovakia” in Russian. The serial number is preceded by CCCP, which is Russian for USSR. This is a Cold War commemorative and, as such, it is important to remember that the Czech Republic (then Czechoslovakia) was a member of the Warsaw Pact.
